# ClaudeGTM .gitignore
# Protect client data and sensitive information

# ==========================================
# CLIENT DATA - NEVER COMMIT
# ==========================================

# Client-specific engagement folders (if they contain sensitive data)
# Uncomment if you want to keep client work local only:
# engagements/active/*/
# engagements/completed/*/

# Client exports and data files
*.csv
*.xlsx
*.xls
*-export.json
*-client-data.*

# Clay table exports with client data
*-client-*.json
clay-exports/

# Client credentials and API keys
*credentials*.json
*.env
.env.*
*apikey*
*api-key*

# ==========================================
# SENSITIVE INTELLIGENCE
# ==========================================

# If you want to keep some intelligence private:
# intelligence/private/
# proprietary-patterns/

# ==========================================
# DEVELOPMENT
# ==========================================

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
venv/
env/
ENV/
.venv

# Node.js (if you build tools)
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# IDEs
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# ==========================================
# INFRASTRUCTURE & TOOLS
# ==========================================

# Database files (if you build tracking tools)
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Logs
*.log
logs/

# Build artifacts
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# Temporary files
tmp/
temp/
*.tmp
*.bak

# ==========================================
# SYSTEM FILES
# ==========================================

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Linux
*~

# ==========================================
# OPTIONAL: ENGAGEMENT DATA
# ==========================================

# Uncomment these if you want more aggressive client data protection:

# All active engagement folders
# engagements/active/

# All completed engagement folders
# engagements/completed/

# Keep only templates
# !engagements/templates/

# ==========================================
# NOTES
# ==========================================

# This .gitignore is configured to:
# 1. Protect client data (CSV, exports, credentials)
# 2. Protect sensitive API keys and credentials
# 3. Ignore standard development artifacts
# 4. Allow intelligence layer to be committed (sanitized)
# 5. Allow templates and documentation

# Adjust based on whether you want to:
# - Keep intelligence private (uncomment intelligence exclusions)
# - Keep all client work local (uncomment engagement exclusions)
# - Share templates publicly (keep templates included)
